      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Veronique" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Veronique" href="/user/show/12371602-veronique">Veronique</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/6506772-murder-in-mesopotamia">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12371602-veronique?shelf=r2020">r2020</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12371602-veronique?shelf=stars-4-0">stars-4-0</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12371602-veronique?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12371602-veronique?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1049278253" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13597747600802905669"><i>“It seems odd that as far as I know nobody has yet been murdered for having too perfect a character! And yet perfection is undoubtedly an irritating thing!”</i><br/><br/>What do you get when you mix a murder mystery with an archeological site full of disparate characters, all far from civilisation? A very entertaining read, that is :0)<br/><br/>Using a side character as narrator was a great move, allowing us access to all parties involved, while creating a likeable protagonist in the nurse. Her voice was so matter of f</span>
  <span id="freeText13597747600802905669" style="display:none"><i>“It seems odd that as far as I know nobody has yet been murdered for having too perfect a character! And yet perfection is undoubtedly an irritating thing!”</i><br /><br />What do you get when you mix a murder mystery with an archeological site full of disparate characters, all far from civilisation? A very entertaining read, that is :0)<br /><br />Using a side character as narrator was a great move, allowing us access to all parties involved, while creating a likeable protagonist in the nurse. Her voice was so matter of fact and funny, especially in her description of our beloved Poirot. Loved it. The plot was also masterfully orchestrated by Christie, leading you one way, then the other, while making you constantly re-evaluate what you think. Fun!</span>
  <a data-text-id="13597747600802905669" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
